Ans 01 :- Mutabale String -- Those Strings which can simply change after declaring once are simply called as Mutable Strings.
          Example:: StringBuilder str = new StringBuilder("Hello");    // Declaring Immutable String
                    str.append("PW"); //Adding PW into the str object

Ans 02 :-   Reverse a string
public static void main(String[] args){
              StringBuilder str = new StringBuilder("Hello");
              str.reverse();
              System.out.println(str);
              }    

Ans 03 :-  Reverse sentence while preserving the position
public static void main(String[] args){
      String str = "Think Twice";
      String str1 = "";
      String[] str2 = str.split(" ");
      for(String str3 : str2){
        for(int i=str3.length()-1;i>=0;i--){
            str1=str1+str.charAt(i);
        }
        str1 = str1+" ";
      }
      System.out.println(str1);
    }    

Ans 04 :- Sorting value programme
 String str = "abedc";
      char[] arr = str.toCharArray();
      Arrays.sort(arr);
      String s = String.valueOf(arr);
      System.out.println(s);
